## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## bmady — BMAD-METHOD-inspired agile delivery, human in the loop
##
## A structured multi-persona pipeline with a human collaboration
## gate between every phase. Each gate is a DIFFERENT kind of
## decision, so one run exercises the whole studio human-interaction
## surface:
##
##   analyst   → elicit_brief    (free-text elicitation)
##   pm        → review_prd      (advanced-elicitation option menu — radio)
##   architect → approve_arch    (document approve / reject — bool)
##             → select_stories  (story multi-select + priority + WIP — checkbox/select/int)
##   dev       → qa              (implement → quality verdict)
##             → final_review    (ship / request_changes / hold — radio)
##                              → commit_changes → done
##
## Personas are plain `agent`/`judge` nodes, one `system:` prompt
## each (the canonical multi-persona pattern from feature-dev). The
## per-persona discipline lives in skills/bmady-<persona>.md, read at
## run time — so adding a stack or changing a persona never touches
## this graph (universal-bot rule).
##
## Reviewer/QA diffs the WORKING TREE (`git diff HEAD`), never the
## last commit — the commit step runs only AFTER the human ships.
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

vars:
  ## ${PROJECT_DIR} resolves to the run worktree under worktree: auto
  ## (do NOT override with a literal repo root — that aims agents at
  ## the main checkout; see CLAUDE.md dogfood note).
  workspace_dir: string = "${PROJECT_DIR}"
  ## The feature / change request. Required — no default.
  brief: string

## ═══ Prompts : personas ══════════════════════════════════════════

prompt analyst_system:
  You are Mary, the BMAD Analyst. You turn a raw request into a
  crisp, testable problem analysis BEFORE anyone writes code. You
  are READ-ONLY: explore the workspace, never modify it.

  Read your operating playbook first, then follow it exactly:

      read_file {{vars.workspace_dir}}/.claude/skills/bmady-analyst.md

  The skill defines the analysis_output contract and the discipline
  (no solutioning, surface the real open questions, name the
  stakeholders). Return the structured analysis_output when done.

prompt analyst_user:
  Request to analyse:
  {{vars.brief}}

  Workspace: {{vars.workspace_dir}}

  Explore read-only, then emit analysis_output. Do not modify any
  file.

prompt pm_system:
  You are John, the BMAD Product Manager. You turn an approved
  problem analysis into a Product Requirements Document: epics, then
  user stories small enough to implement, each with acceptance
  criteria.

  Read your playbook first:

      read_file {{vars.workspace_dir}}/.claude/skills/bmady-pm.md

  IMPORTANT: every story in `stories` MUST carry a stable `id`
  (e.g. "S1", "S2") and a one-line `title` — the operator selects
  stories by id downstream, so missing ids break the workflow.

prompt pm_user:
  Problem analysis (approved):
  {{input.analysis}}

  Operator clarifications gathered after analysis:
  {{input.clarifications}}

  Refinement requested by the operator on the previous PRD draft
  (empty on the first pass — when set, address it specifically):
  {{input.refinement}}
  {{input.feedback}}

  Produce the PRD as prd_output. Keep stories small and id'd.

prompt architect_system:
  You are Winston, the BMAD Architect. You turn an approved PRD into
  a pragmatic architecture: the shape of the solution, the key
  components, the ADR-worthy decisions, and the risks. READ-ONLY —
  you design, you do not implement.

  Read your playbook first:

      read_file {{vars.workspace_dir}}/.claude/skills/bmady-architect.md

prompt architect_user:
  PRD (approved):
  {{input.prd}}

  Problem analysis:
  {{input.analysis}}

  Operator feedback on the previous architecture draft (empty on the
  first pass — when set, address it specifically):
  {{input.feedback}}

  Produce arch_output. Anchor every decision to a PRD story or risk.

prompt dev_system:
  You are James, the BMAD Developer. You implement EXACTLY the
  stories the operator selected, against the approved architecture.
  Mutating tools are allowed. Do NOT commit — a downstream step
  commits only after QA and the operator sign off.

  Read your playbook first:

      read_file {{vars.workspace_dir}}/.claude/skills/bmady-dev.md

  Run the project's own tests after each meaningful change. Stay
  inside the selected stories' scope; if a selected story turns out
  to be unrealistic, implement what you can and record the deviation
  in `pushback`.

prompt dev_user:
  Implement the SELECTED stories in {{vars.workspace_dir}}.

  Selected story ids: {{input.selected_story_ids}}
  WIP limit (max stories to carry in parallel): {{input.wip_limit}}
  Operator note: {{input.note}}

  All stories (for reference — implement only the selected ids):
  {{input.stories}}

  Approved architecture:
  {{input.architecture_doc}}

  Operator change request from the previous QA round (empty on the
  first pass — when set, fix exactly this):
  {{input.feedback}}

  Apply the changes, run the tests, then emit dev_output. Do NOT
  run `git commit`.

prompt qa_system:
  You are Quinn, the BMAD QA architect. You judge the work that was
  just implemented in this run.

  MANDATORY FIRST ACTION — before any verdict, run
  `git -C {{vars.workspace_dir}} status` and
  `git -C {{vars.workspace_dir}} diff HEAD` (read-only; prepend
  `-c safe.directory='*'` if git reports dubious ownership) to obtain
  the actual changes. The work is UNCOMMITTED in the working tree —
  diff against HEAD, NEVER `HEAD^...HEAD` (that shows the base and
  makes you wrongly conclude nothing was implemented).

  Read your playbook first:

      read_file {{vars.workspace_dir}}/.claude/skills/bmady-qa.md

  Judge correctness, security, robustness, tests, and whether the
  implemented work satisfies the SELECTED stories' acceptance
  criteria. Report only real, production-blocking issues in
  `blockers` — preferences and pre-existing unrelated code are not
  blockers. Set `confidence` honestly.

prompt qa_user:
  Stories that were in scope this round:
  {{input.selected_story_ids}}

  Developer's summary of what was done:
  {{input.dev_summary}}

  Diff the working tree, audit it, and emit qa_output.

## ═══ Prompts : human gate instructions (rendered in the form) ═════

prompt elicit_brief_instructions:
  # Clarify the brief

  Mary analysed the request. Before John drafts the PRD, fill any
  gaps she surfaced.

  **Problem statement**

  {{input.problem_statement}}

  **Proposed scope**

  {{input.proposed_scope}}

  **Open questions Mary needs you to answer**

  {{input.open_questions}}

  Answer what you can and add any constraint, preference, or context
  that should shape the plan. Free-form — bullet points are fine. You
  can also _Skip_ if the analysis is already complete.

prompt review_prd_instructions:
  # Review the PRD

  John drafted the Product Requirements Document.

  **Epics**

  {{input.epics}}

  **User stories**

  {{input.stories}}

  **Acceptance criteria**

  {{input.acceptance}}

  Choose how to proceed:

  - **approve** — the PRD is good; move on to architecture.
  - **expand** — flesh out a thin epic or story (say which in the feedback).
  - **add_risks** — call out risks / edge cases John missed.
  - **revise** — change scope or priorities (describe the change).

  Put any detail for `expand` / `add_risks` / `revise` in the
  feedback box.

prompt approve_arch_instructions:
  # Approve the architecture

  Winston proposed the architecture for the approved PRD.

  **Architecture**

  {{input.architecture_doc}}

  **Key components**

  {{input.components}}

  **Risks**

  {{input.risks}}

  **Approve** to proceed to story selection, or **Reject** and tell
  Winston what to change in the feedback box.

prompt select_stories_instructions:
  # Select stories to implement now

  Pick the stories James should implement in this round. Anything you
  leave unchecked stays on the backlog.

  **Available stories**

  {{input.stories}}

  **Architecture (for reference)**

  {{input.architecture_doc}}

  - **Stories** — tick the ones to build now.
  - **Priority** — where this slice sits in the plan.
  - **WIP limit** — how many stories James should carry in parallel.
  - **Note** — anything James should keep in mind.

prompt final_review_instructions:
  # Sign off

  Quinn finished QA on the implemented work.

  **Passed:** {{input.passed}}
  **Confidence:** {{input.confidence}}

  **Blockers**

  {{input.blockers}}

  **Developer summary**

  {{input.dev_summary}}

  Decide:

  - **ship** — accept the work; iterion commits it and the run ends.
  - **request_changes** — send it back to James with your notes.
  - **hold_for_later** — stop without committing (keep the worktree).

## ═══ Schemas ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

schema analysis_output:
  problem_statement: string
  stakeholders: string[]
  open_questions: string[]
  proposed_scope: string
  rationale: string

schema elicit_input:
  problem_statement: string
  proposed_scope: string
  open_questions: string[]

schema elicit_output:
  clarifications: string

schema prd_input:
  analysis: json
  clarifications: string
  ## refinement/feedback are set only on the revise loop edge.
  refinement: string
  feedback: string

schema prd_output:
  epics: json
  ## stories MUST be an array of objects each with `id` + `title`
  ## (the operator multi-selects by id downstream).
  stories: json
  acceptance: string[]
  rationale: string

schema review_prd_input:
  epics: json
  stories: json
  acceptance: string[]

schema review_prd_output:
  action: string [enum: "approve", "expand", "add_risks", "revise"]
  feedback: string

schema prd_derived:
  is_approve: bool
  action: string
  feedback: string

schema arch_input:
  prd: json
  analysis: json
  feedback: string

schema arch_output:
  architecture_doc: string
  components: string[]
  adrs: json
  risks: string[]
  rationale: string

schema approve_arch_input:
  architecture_doc: string
  components: string[]
  risks: string[]

schema approve_arch_output:
  approved: bool
  feedback: string

schema select_stories_input:
  stories: json
  architecture_doc: string

schema select_stories_output:
  ## selected_story_ids renders as a checkbox column over the sibling
  ## `stories` array in the questions context (formSpecFromSchema
  ## selection-field detection: name starts "selected_" / ends "_ids").
  selected_story_ids: json
  priority: string [enum: "now", "next", "later", "backlog", "icebox"]
  wip_limit: int
  note: string

schema dev_input:
  selected_story_ids: json
  stories: json
  architecture_doc: string
  wip_limit: int
  note: string
  feedback: string

schema dev_output:
  applied: bool
  summary: string
  files: string[]
  pushback: string[]

schema qa_input:
  selected_story_ids: json
  dev_summary: string

schema qa_output:
  passed: bool
  blockers: string[]
  confidence: string [enum: "low", "medium", "high"]
  scanned_areas: string[]

schema final_input:
  passed: bool
  blockers: string[]
  confidence: string
  dev_summary: string

schema final_output:
  action: string [enum: "ship", "request_changes", "hold_for_later"]
  feedback: string

schema final_derived:
  is_ship: bool
  is_changes: bool
  action: string
  feedback: string

schema commit_tool_input:
  workspace_dir: string
  message: string

schema commit_result:
  success: bool
  output: string

## ═══ Nodes ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

agent analyst:
  backend: "claude_code"
  model: "${BMADY_MODEL_CLAUDE:-claude-opus-4-8}"
  reasoning_effort: "${BMADY_EFFORT_PLAN:-high}"
  output: analysis_output
  system: analyst_system
  user: analyst_user
  session: fresh
  tools: [bash, read_file, glob, grep]
  tool_max_steps: 40
  readonly: true

human elicit_brief:
  input: elicit_input
  output: elicit_output
  instructions: elicit_brief_instructions
  interaction: human

agent pm:
  backend: "claude_code"
  model: "${BMADY_MODEL_CLAUDE:-claude-opus-4-8}"
  reasoning_effort: "${BMADY_EFFORT_PLAN:-high}"
  input: prd_input
  output: prd_output
  system: pm_system
  user: pm_user
  session: fresh
  tools: [bash, read_file, glob, grep]
  tool_max_steps: 30
  readonly: true

human review_prd:
  input: review_prd_input
  output: review_prd_output
  instructions: review_prd_instructions
  interaction: human

## Project the elicitation menu into the boolean the routing reads —
## keeps `action` (4 options) in the form while the graph branches on
## a clean approve / not-approve pair.
compute derive_prd:
  input: review_prd_output
  output: prd_derived
  expr:
    is_approve: "input.action == 'approve'"
    action: "input.action"
    feedback: "input.feedback"

agent architect:
  backend: "claude_code"
  model: "${BMADY_MODEL_CLAUDE:-claude-opus-4-8}"
  reasoning_effort: "${BMADY_EFFORT_PLAN:-high}"
  input: arch_input
  output: arch_output
  system: architect_system
  user: architect_user
  session: fresh
  tools: [bash, read_file, glob, grep]
  tool_max_steps: 30
  readonly: true

human approve_arch:
  input: approve_arch_input
  output: approve_arch_output
  instructions: approve_arch_instructions
  interaction: human

human select_stories:
  input: select_stories_input
  output: select_stories_output
  instructions: select_stories_instructions
  interaction: human

agent dev:
  backend: "claude_code"
  model: "${BMADY_MODEL_CLAUDE:-claude-opus-4-8}"
  reasoning_effort: "${BMADY_EFFORT_DEV:-high}"
  input: dev_input
  output: dev_output
  system: dev_system
  user: dev_user
  session: fresh
  tools: [bash, read_file, write_file, file_edit, glob, grep]
  tool_max_steps: 120

judge qa:
  backend: "claude_code"
  model: "${BMADY_MODEL_QA:-claude-opus-4-8}"
  reasoning_effort: "${BMADY_EFFORT_QA:-medium}"
  input: qa_input
  output: qa_output
  system: qa_system
  user: qa_user
  session: fresh
  tools: [bash, read_file, glob, grep]
  tool_max_steps: 30
  readonly: true

human final_review:
  input: final_input
  output: final_output
  instructions: final_review_instructions
  interaction: human

compute derive_final:
  input: final_output
  output: final_derived
  expr:
    is_ship: "input.action == 'ship'"
    is_changes: "input.action == 'request_changes'"
    action: "input.action"
    feedback: "input.feedback"

## Deterministic commit — no LLM. `git add -A` is safe because
## worktree: auto means the whole dirty tree IS this run's work.
## Guarded so an empty diff doesn't error.
tool commit_changes:
  command: "git -C {{input.workspace_dir}} add -A && (git -C {{input.workspace_dir}} diff --cached --quiet || git -C {{input.workspace_dir}} commit -m {{input.message}})"
  input: commit_tool_input
  output: commit_result

## ═══ Workflow ════════════════════════════════════════════════════

workflow bmady:
  entry: analyst

  ## Isolate every mutation in a fresh git worktree. On a clean ship
  ## the engine persists the commit to a branch and fast-forwards the
  ## operator's checked-out branch (override with --merge-into).
  worktree: auto

  budget:
    max_parallel_branches: 1
    ## Caps a single autonomous BURST between two human pauses — the
    ## runtime suspends the budget while paused, so a multi-day
    ## collaborative session never accumulates against these.
    max_duration: "4h"
    max_cost_usd: 50
    max_iterations: 60

  ## ── Phase 1 : Analysis ──────────────────────────────────────────
  analyst -> elicit_brief with {
    problem_statement: "{{outputs.analyst.problem_statement}}",
    proposed_scope:    "{{outputs.analyst.proposed_scope}}",
    open_questions:    "{{outputs.analyst.open_questions}}"
  }

  ## ── Phase 2 : PRD (+ advanced-elicitation revise loop) ──────────
  elicit_brief -> pm with {
    analysis:       "{{outputs.analyst}}",
    clarifications: "{{outputs.elicit_brief.clarifications}}"
  }

  pm -> review_prd with {
    epics:      "{{outputs.pm.epics}}",
    stories:    "{{outputs.pm.stories}}",
    acceptance: "{{outputs.pm.acceptance}}"
  }

  review_prd -> derive_prd with {
    action:   "{{outputs.review_prd.action}}",
    feedback: "{{outputs.review_prd.feedback}}"
  }

  ## approve → architecture ; anything else → John revises (bounded).
  derive_prd -> architect when is_approve with {
    prd:      "{{outputs.pm}}",
    analysis: "{{outputs.analyst}}"
  }
  derive_prd -> pm when not is_approve as prd_loop(5) with {
    analysis:       "{{outputs.analyst}}",
    clarifications: "{{outputs.elicit_brief.clarifications}}",
    refinement:     "{{outputs.derive_prd.action}}",
    feedback:       "{{outputs.derive_prd.feedback}}"
  }

  ## ── Phase 3 : Architecture (+ approve/reject loop) ──────────────
  architect -> approve_arch with {
    architecture_doc: "{{outputs.architect.architecture_doc}}",
    components:       "{{outputs.architect.components}}",
    risks:            "{{outputs.architect.risks}}"
  }

  approve_arch -> select_stories when approved with {
    stories:          "{{outputs.pm.stories}}",
    architecture_doc: "{{outputs.architect.architecture_doc}}"
  }
  approve_arch -> architect when not approved as arch_loop(5) with {
    prd:      "{{outputs.pm}}",
    analysis: "{{outputs.analyst}}",
    feedback: "{{outputs.approve_arch.feedback}}"
  }

  ## ── Phase 4 : Story selection → implement ───────────────────────
  select_stories -> dev with {
    selected_story_ids: "{{outputs.select_stories.selected_story_ids}}",
    stories:            "{{outputs.pm.stories}}",
    architecture_doc:   "{{outputs.architect.architecture_doc}}",
    wip_limit:          "{{outputs.select_stories.wip_limit}}",
    note:               "{{outputs.select_stories.note}}"
  }

  ## ── Phase 5 : QA → sign-off (+ change loop) ─────────────────────
  dev -> qa with {
    selected_story_ids: "{{outputs.select_stories.selected_story_ids}}",
    dev_summary:        "{{outputs.dev.summary}}"
  }

  qa -> final_review with {
    passed:      "{{outputs.qa.passed}}",
    blockers:    "{{outputs.qa.blockers}}",
    confidence:  "{{outputs.qa.confidence}}",
    dev_summary: "{{outputs.dev.summary}}"
  }

  final_review -> derive_final with {
    action:   "{{outputs.final_review.action}}",
    feedback: "{{outputs.final_review.feedback}}"
  }

  ## ship → commit ; request_changes → James (bounded) ; hold/other →
  ## the unconditional fallback ends the run without committing.
  derive_final -> commit_changes when is_ship with {
    workspace_dir: "{{vars.workspace_dir}}",
    message:       "feat(bmady): {{vars.brief}}"
  }
  derive_final -> dev when is_changes as dev_loop(5) with {
    selected_story_ids: "{{outputs.select_stories.selected_story_ids}}",
    stories:            "{{outputs.pm.stories}}",
    architecture_doc:   "{{outputs.architect.architecture_doc}}",
    wip_limit:          "{{outputs.select_stories.wip_limit}}",
    note:               "{{outputs.select_stories.note}}",
    feedback:           "{{outputs.derive_final.feedback}}"
  }
  derive_final -> done

  commit_changes -> done
